Description: Fragment of a plaster jar sealing; right part of the outer convex surface bears a complete cartouche of a king Psamtek stamped in low relief and, on the left and on the top, part of two other ones. The inner concave part shows the negative impression of the shoulder of the sealed pottery and numerous horizontal and slanted negative traces which cross each other, show the negative impression of the straw string attaching the lid to the neck of the jar. The cartouche is vertical and surmounted by a solar disc between two ostrich feathers.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, Findspot 8, west of the "Qasr"
Curator's comments: The Findspot number 8 has been scratched into the object.. See also Bolton, 1886.28.112 and London, BM, EA 23792, both coming from the same Findspot 8, the latter showing a negative impression of the same stamp.
